                        <div class="heading-title heading-line-double">
                            <h2>Factor Three: <span>Workplace Accountability Matters</span></h2>
                        </div>
                        <p>Doing it right is what leads to getting it done!  Workforce Optimization is also the appropriate intervention in an employee's experience to foster the best possible reuslts, which includes avoiding the negative inhibitors.</p>
                        <p>Most companies already have results accountability.  They call them Annual Reviews.  The problem is that annual reviews don't change results.  Even if you switch to quarterly reviews, they don't get to the root of the problem.</p>
                        <p>The root of employee job performance improvement is training and continual coaching.  The FOCUS on the UNDERLYING BEHAVIORS is what brings about the improved results.</p>
                        <h4 class="text-center"><span>By adding accountability to process (doing it right) you increase the learning transfer.</span></h4>
                        <p>Tackle one performance improvement at a time, through a focused review of the performance of a job task, to effectively change the person's underlying habit.  Focus on one - you'll get it done!</p>
                        <h4>More on Employee Reviews</h4>
                    </div>
